  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6828.51 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6820 (-29.7B) and positive gamma at 6840 (+24.5B), dealers are caught in a whipsaw zone where they're forced to buy any dips toward 6820 and sell any rallies toward 6840, creating amplified volatility. The -3.9B total GEX and BREAKOUT regime confirms dealers are net short gamma, meaning they'll accelerate moves in either direction rather than provide stability. The 6820-6840 corridor is the critical battleground - a break below 6820 triggers dealer buying that could fuel momentum lower, while a push above 6840 forces dealer selling into strength.\n\n**Bottom line: expect violent swings between 6820-6840 with potential for explosive moves if either level breaks.**",
